The following logged message is interesting...
{code}
[WARN]  zygote: Unexpected CPU variant for X86 using defaults: x86_64
{code}

Sounds like an x86 architecture issue. Like your module might be missing an x86 .so for the module.

If you unzip your APK file (ie: change the {{.apk}} extension to {{.zip}} and then unzip it), then you can find all of the {{.so}} libraries under the unzipped APK's "lib" folder. You should have a matching {{.so}} library under every architecture subfolder such as "x86" and "armeabi-v7a". If there is a different amount of libraries under the subfolders, then that's the problem.
